{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T12:09+0000", "md5": "C162CF2074D45797B35FB4AC1185D7AB", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SegmOnto", "normalizedForm": "SegmOnto", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "SegmOnto has already been implemented in several projects led by Pinche and connected to the CREMMALab project such as Gabay et al. (2022), resulting in segmentation models mainly for late medieval manuscripts and early prints. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021284818649291992}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.026514172554016113}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.11945056915283203}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.057219505310058594}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SegmOnto", "normalizedForm": "SegmOnto", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "SegmOnto offers multiple levels of description, of which only the first is completely standardized, as the second is intended for custom refinement and the third for local and document-based differentiation. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.445148468017578e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004170536994934082}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.11945056915283203}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.057219505310058594}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SegmOnto", "normalizedForm": "SegmOnto", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "SegmOnto was born out of the need for a small/restricted common ontology based on existing standards for the description and analysis of document layout, ranging from content categorization to text recognition, mainly addressing the case of manuscripts and early printed books.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006142854690551758}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.057219505310058594}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.11945056915283203}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.057219505310058594}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 10}, "context": "The CREMMA funding consisted of a grant for the initial cost of the infrastructure as well as an evaluation grant for providing base models for the community of CREMMA's users.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9955169558525085}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00031554698944091797}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.6954879760742188e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 7, "offsetEnd": 13}, "context": "Unlike CREMMA Medieval, our approach has been feature-driven to compensate for rare characters in the dataset network. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001849532127380371}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 7, "offsetEnd": 13}, "context": "As the CREMMA project was being drafted, Chagu\u00e9 and Cl\u00e9rice (2020) provided a solution for facilitating the FAIR principles in an HTR context and providing machine-actionable metadata for datasets.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00014066696166992188}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.5595847964286804}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 12, "offsetEnd": 18}, "context": "The project CREMMA was funded by the DIM MAP (now DIM PAMIR) under the supervision of the Conseil R\u00e9gional d'\u00cele de France.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9773554801940918}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0020244717597961426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.9073486328125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 13, "offsetEnd": 19}, "context": "7 As per the CREMMA Medii Aevi dataset, the documents present two kinds of layout: multi-columns and singular columns, for which lines are most often long, except for the Psalms and Book of Hours.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.007086694240570068}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.895427703857422e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 16, "offsetEnd": 22}, "context": "Absent from the CREMMA Medieval but present in Medii Aevi, the truncated ending -is is transcribed using the character \ua76d (U+A76D).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.7114276885986328}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.7523765563964844e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SegmOnto", "normalizedForm": "SegmOnto", "offsetStart": 25, "offsetEnd": 33}, "context": "Segmentation vocabulary: SegmOnto With the emergence of efficient layout analyzers and easy-to-use interfaces, the need for efficient segmentation models increases (as does the need for large amounts of data) based on the aggregation of heterogeneous documents. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.410743713378906e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00033974647521972656}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.11945056915283203}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.057219505310058594}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "eScriptorium", "normalizedForm": "eScriptorium", "offsetStart": 25, "offsetEnd": 37}, "context": "The data was built using eScriptorium and Kraken for both segmentation of zones and lines (specifically the BLLA model).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999077320098877}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 8.761882781982422e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999077320098877}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006831884384155273}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.838539123535156e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "eScriptorium", "normalizedForm": "eScriptorium", "offsetStart": 28, "offsetEnd": 40}, "context": "Alongside text recognition, eScriptorium allows for layout annotation using ontologies and controlled vocabularies. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006831884384155273}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999077320098877}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006831884384155273}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.838539123535156e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 29, "offsetEnd": 35}, "context": "Character frequencies in the CREMMA Medieval and the Medii Aevi datasets We set up this corpus to both complement the CREMMA Medieval dataset and grow the available set of data for Latin through the Middle Ages, noting that at least two datasets for Medieval Latin existed already (Caroline Minuscule and Eutyches) in abbreviated form for pre-10 th century documents.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9751748442649841}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.838539123535156e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMALab", "normalizedForm": "CREMMALab", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 39}, "context": "As the first recipient of the CREMMALab post-doctoral funding, Pinche co-organized a research seminar around the formalization of transcription guidelines for graphemic transcription of Old French (Pinche, 2022c).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0025028586387634277}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8122140169143677}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987844824790955}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8122140169143677}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.6689300537109375e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 46, "offsetEnd": 52}, "context": "Only three characters are more represented in CREMMA Medieval: the Tironian Et, the superscript combining R (common on words such as \"grand\"), and \"&\". ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.01771324872970581}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.710124969482422e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ChocoMufin", "normalizedForm": "ChocoMufin", "offsetStart": 49, "offsetEnd": 59}, "context": "Each manuscript transcription was passed through ChocoMufin (Cl\u00e9rice & Pinche, 2021), using project-provided character translation and control tables.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998772144317627}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.6464462280273438e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998772144317627}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.35385513305664e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "references": [{"label": "(Cl\u00e9rice & Pinche, 2021)", "normalizedForm": "Cl\u00e9rice & Pinche, 2021", "refKey": 0, "offsetStart": 16012, "offsetEnd": 16036}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ChocoMufin", "normalizedForm": "ChocoMufin", "offsetStart": 55, "offsetEnd": 65}, "context": "Using the project-provided character conversion table, ChocoMufin controls the transcription and corrects any anticipated error by transforming the character automatically so it conforms to the pre-defined guidelines (data should be used in their post-ChocoMufin converted state as it sometimes corrected mistranscription).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.013711214065551758}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.35385513305664e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998772144317627}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.35385513305664e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "references": [{"label": "(Cl\u00e9rice & Pinche, 2021)", "normalizedForm": "Cl\u00e9rice & Pinche, 2021", "refKey": 0}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SegmOnto", "normalizedForm": "SegmOnto", "offsetStart": 57, "offsetEnd": 65}, "context": "For the purposes of the project, only the first level of SegmOnto has been utilized, such as MainZone for columns and MargintextZone for marginalia.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004462599754333496}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.704692840576172e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.11945056915283203}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.057219505310058594}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 64, "offsetEnd": 70}, "context": "12In general, the main differences that we isolated between the CREMMA Medieval and Medii Aevi datasets, stemming from the language as well as the genre's own characteristics, are:", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.0411949157714844e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 65, "offsetEnd": 71}, "context": "11 This process has been largely used in the first months of the CREMMA Medieval project, as the guidelines were still being drafted.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.07632935047149658}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.001301884651184082}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 84, "offsetEnd": 90}, "context": "Our dataset builds on the experience of Ariane Pinche, specifically her work on the CREMMA Medieval dataset, which treats different variations of Old French from the 13 th to the 15 th century, with a heavy focus on the first section of the period.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004885196685791016}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9557315707206726}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ChocoMufin", "normalizedForm": "ChocoMufin", "offsetStart": 84, "offsetEnd": 94}, "context": "Once each sample is entirely annotated, its use of characters is controlled via the ChocoMufin software, while its conformity to the segmentation classification vocabulary is controlled by HTRVX. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9650678634643555}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.288818359375e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998772144317627}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.35385513305664e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "references": [{"label": "(Cl\u00e9rice & Pinche, 2021)", "normalizedForm": "Cl\u00e9rice & Pinche, 2021", "refKey": 0}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMALab", "normalizedForm": "CREMMALab", "offsetStart": 93, "offsetEnd": 102}, "context": "SegmOnto has already been implemented in several projects led by Pinche and connected to the CREMMALab project such as Gabay et al. (2022), resulting in segmentation models mainly for late medieval manuscripts and early prints.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021284818649291992}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.026514172554016113}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987844824790955}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8122140169143677}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.6689300537109375e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 100, "offsetEnd": 106}, "context": "Based on her recommendations, a few datasets emerged around the \u00c9cole nationale des chartes and the CREMMA project.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8582172989845276}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021725893020629883}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 102, "offsetEnd": 108}, "context": "In this context, the Consortium pour la Reconnaissance d'\u00c9critures Manuscrites des Mat\u00e9riaux Anciens (CREMMA) project was created to fund a regional server.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.02107703685760498}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.01845473051071167}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMALab", "normalizedForm": "CREMMALab", "offsetStart": 107, "offsetEnd": 116}, "context": "It also allows for project-specific transcription guidelines to be translated to a more common one such as CREMMALab's (Pinche & Camps, 2022). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.0677528381347656e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001271963119506836}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.6689300537109375e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9987844824790955}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8122140169143677}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.6689300537109375e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 111, "offsetEnd": 117}, "context": "A postdoctoral position, CREMMAlab provided the infrastructure with complementary time for building a dataset (CREMMA Medieval) and expertise around transcribing medieval manuscripts.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.003737032413482666}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.10489195585250854}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 118, "offsetEnd": 124}, "context": "Character frequencies in the CREMMA Medieval and the Medii Aevi datasets We set up this corpus to both complement the CREMMA Medieval dataset and grow the available set of data for Latin through the Middle Ages, noting that at least two datasets for Medieval Latin existed already (Caroline Minuscule and Eutyches) in abbreviated form for pre-10 th century documents.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9751748442649841}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.838539123535156e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 135, "offsetEnd": 141}, "context": "The collection was built not to be representative of one specific use of the Latin language and is not thematically unified, while the CREMMA Medieval dataset focuses more on literary texts, specifically hagiographic and chanson de geste texts.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.2611425518989563}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00020736455917358398}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "eScriptorium", "normalizedForm": "eScriptorium", "offsetStart": 146, "offsetEnd": 158}, "context": "16 All the combining and abbreviation signs suggested for use by the present adaptation of Pinche's guidelines can be also found on a custom-made eScriptorium keyboard configuration, in order to facilitate reuse and compatibility with the guidelines.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.003280937671661377}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00030100345611572266}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.838539123535156e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999077320098877}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006831884384155273}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.838539123535156e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "eScriptorium", "normalizedForm": "eScriptorium", "offsetStart": 152, "offsetEnd": 164}, "context": "2 At the end of the 2020 European Union funding, Transkribus became a paid service accelerating the interest growth of at least one alternative, namely eScriptorium (Kiessling, Tissot, Stokes, & Ezra, 2019) at the EPHE-Scripta-PSL.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.001184701919555664}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.665157318115234e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0371208190917969e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999077320098877}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006831884384155273}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.838539123535156e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 161, "offsetEnd": 167}, "context": "The CREMMA funding consisted of a grant for the initial cost of the infrastructure as well as an evaluation grant for providing base models for the community of CREMMA's users.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9955169558525085}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00031554698944091797}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.6954879760742188e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMALab", "normalizedForm": "CREMMALab", "offsetStart": 165, "offsetEnd": 174}, "context": "Part of the alignment of data for the Faithful Transcription Data Set and the complete writing time for this paper was done under the funding of the 