, "score": 0.057219505310058594}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 252, "offsetEnd": 258}, "context": "The section that follows aims to guide the reader through the transcription norms followed for the Medii Aevi dataset, illustrating the process and the more common and complex cases, especially where new characters have been introduced compared to the CREMMA Medieval dataset.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.012751519680023193}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006765127182006836}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ChocoMufin", "normalizedForm": "ChocoMufin", "offsetStart": 252, "offsetEnd": 262}, "context": "Using the project-provided character conversion table, ChocoMufin controls the transcription and corrects any anticipated error by transforming the character automatically so it conforms to the pre-defined guidelines (data should be used in their post-ChocoMufin converted state as it sometimes corrected mistranscription).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.013711214065551758}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.35385513305664e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998772144317627}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.35385513305664e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "references": [{"label": "(Cl\u00e9rice & Pinche, 2021)", "normalizedForm": "Cl\u00e9rice & Pinche, 2021", "refKey": 0}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CREMMA", "normalizedForm": "CREMMA", "offsetStart": 365, "offsetEnd": 371}, "context": "This improvement derives equally from the simple addition of Latin into the model, as shown by the clear gap between the mixed model with Carolingian data: not only the model might benefit from Latin in general (as potentially shown by the simple addition of the Carolingian data), but it also gains in performance out of the amount of data from the same period as CREMMA Medieval. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.05027163028717041}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.841255187988281e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988061189651489}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9624617695808411}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}}}], "references": [{"refKey": 0, "tei": "<biblStruct xml:id=\"b0\">\n\t<analytic>\n\t\t<title level=\"a\" type=\"main\">CREMMA Medii Aevi: Literary Manuscript Text Recognition in Latin</title>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">Thibault</forename><surname>Cl\u00e9rice</surname></persName>\n\t\t\t<idno type=\"ORCID\">0000-0003-1852-9204</idno>\n\t\t</author>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">Malamatenia</forename><surname>Vlachou-Efstathiou</surname></persName>\n\t\t\t<idno type=\"ORCID\">0000-0002-9397-356X</idno>\n\t\t</author>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">Alix</forename><surname>Chagu\u00e9</surname></persName>\n\t\t\t<idno type=\"ORCID\">0000-0002-0136-4434</idno>\n\t\t</author>\n\t\t<idno type=\"DOI\">10.5334/johd.97</idno>\n\t\t<idno>4C3182CD6438454532D155631F0ED5FE</idno>\n\t</analytic>\n\t<monogr>\n\t\t<title level=\"j\">Journal of Open Humanities Data</title>\n\t\t<title level=\"j\" type=\"abbrev\">JOHD</title>\n\t\t<idno type=\"ISSNe\">2059-481X</idno>\